HEADWORD: Mannheim gold
<hw>Mann"heim gold"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From <ets>Mannheim</ets> in
Germany, where much of it was made.]</ety> <def>A kind of brass made in
imitation of gold. It contains eighty per cent of copper and twenty of
zinc.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mannide</ent>⟦br⟧
